{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-01-19",
 "title": "First Inspection of the NRS Internuncio",
 "summary": "In a New Republic hangar bay, the diplomatic pilot Bazil McKenzie brings in his brand-new freighter, the NRS Internuncio, for its first inspection. Sergeant Lianna Blackledge of Support Ops, freshly back on duty and pointedly calm, is wrapping up a stern talk with a reluctant technician about mandatory zero-G training when she crosses paths with the distracted pilot. After he inadvertently leans on a crate she needs to catalog, the two strike up a businesslike exchange about the ship's rough handling and shaky repulsorlifts. Lianna logs a work order and estimates a couple of hours to realign the repulsor system on the freshly built vessel, then signs off shift with a dry warning to avoid the mess-hall jello as both head for the elevators.",
